    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nRunning nvim and immediately pressing `<Ctrl-O>` or issuing `:ju` command causes nvim to freeze for 20+ seconds before the jump to file occurs / jumplist appears. Thereafter, `<Ctrl-O>`, `:ju` and `<Ctrl-I>` are responsive.\r\n\r\nThe problem appears to be resolved if all the filepaths in the jumplist are available. In my case, the jumplist contains references to files like X:\\dev\\xyz.txt, where drive X: is mapped to a network share that is unavailable some of the time. When files on X: are available, jumplist commands on startup are immediate as expected. When X: is disconnected / offline, the problem occurs the first time jumplist commands are issued after startup.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-2663+gc1c6c1ee1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nunable to test\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 10\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWindows Terminal preview\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nNightly win64 build",
