            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "It doesn't appear to make any difference. But my jumplist also contains references to UNC paths like `\\\\machine\\share\\file.txt`. So I tried `:set shada+=r\\\\machine\\share` in addition to your suggestion but neither/both have any effect on the delay with `ju` or `<Ctrl-O>`. So I think this may be a different issue. When `\\\\machine\\share` is available - which is also the share that X: maps to - there are no delays.\r\n\r\nI experience no other issues, eg. delays when quitting nvim and, in case unclear, the shada file is stored on the local (C:) drive.",
